claims:
1. An aircraft comprising:
a fuselage extending between a forward end and an aft end;
a forward wing assembly attached to or formed integrally with the fuselage proximate the forward end of the fuselage;
an aft wing assembly attached to or formed integrally with the fuselage proximate the aft end of the fuselage;
a propulsion system comprising
a port forward propulsor and a starboard forward propulsor, the port and starboard forward propulsors each attached to the forward wing assembly on opposing sides of the fuselage and rotatable between a forward thrust position and a vertical thrust position;
a port aft propulsor and a starboard aft propulsor, the port and starboard aft propulsors each attached to the aft wing assembly on opposing sides of the fuselage and rotatable between a forward thrust position and a vertical thrust position; and
a supplemental propulsor mounted to the fuselage, wherein the supplemental propulsor is a ducted supplemental fan comprising an outer nacelle and a tail cone, wherein the supplemental propulsor further comprises a thrust augmenter moveable between a forward thrust position and a vertical thrust position, and wherein the thrust augmenter is integrated into the outer nacelle, the tail cone, or both.

12. A propulsion system for an aircraft, the aircraft comprising a wing assembly attached to or formed integrally with a fuselage, the propulsion system comprising:
an electric generator;
a combustion engine coupled to the electric generator for driving the electric generator, the electric generator configured to generate electrical power;
a port propulsor and a starboard propulsor, the port and starboard propulsors each configured for attachment to the wing assembly on opposing sides of the fuselage and rotatable between a forward thrust position and a vertical thrust position, the port and starboard propulsors each configured as electric propulsors in electrical communication with the electric generator;
a supplemental propulsor configured to be mounted to the fuselage, the combustion engine mechanically coupled to the supplemental propulsor for driving the supplemental propulsor; and
a gearbox, and wherein the combustion engine is mechanically coupled to the supplemental propulsor through the gearbox.

17. An aircraft comprising:
a fuselage extending between a forward end and an aft end;
a forward wing assembly attached to or formed integrally with the fuselage proximate the forward end of the fuselage;
an aft wing assembly attached to or formed integrally with the fuselage proximate the aft end of the fuselage; and
a propulsion system comprising
an electric generator;
a combustion engine coupled to the electric generator for driving the electric generator, the electric generator configured to generate electrical power;
a port forward propulsor and a starboard forward propulsor, the port and starboard forward propulsors each attached to the forward wing assembly on opposing sides of the fuselage and rotatable between a forward thrust position and a vertical thrust position, the port and starboard forward propulsors each configured as electric propulsors in electrical communication with the electric generator;
a port aft propulsor and a starboard aft propulsor, the port and starboard aft propulsors each attached to the aft wing assembly on opposing sides of the fuselage and rotatable between a forward thrust position and a vertical thrust position, the port and starboard aft propulsors each configured as electric propulsors in electrical communication with the electric generator;
a supplemental propulsor mounted to the fuselage, the combustion engine mechanically coupled to the supplemental propulsor for driving the supplemental propulsor; and
a gearbox, and wherein the combustion engine is mechanically coupled to the supplemental propulsor through the gearbox.
